 <body>
  <h1>
   event_action
   <span>
    DEPRECATED
   </span>
  </h1>
  This
  <b>
   read-only
  </b>
  variable returns the index of the action currently being executed, starting at 0 on previous versions of GameMaker. However, this is
  <b>
   now an obsolete variable
  </b>
  in
  <span>
   GameMaker
  </span>
  . It has been left in for legacy support only, and will
  <b>
   always return 0
  </b>
  as all actions are concatenated together to improve execution speed.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">event_action;
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">num = event_action;
</code></pre>
  The above code stores the current action number in the variable "num".
 </body>
</html>